South Africans are urged to make their voices count by voting for the reigning Miss South Africa, Ntandoyenkosi Kunene, to help her secure a spot in the Miss Universe top 12 ahead of the finale in Manila on January 30.Kunene is representing SA against 85 other countries. Online voting opened at 4am today and will close a day prior to the Monday live event which will be broadcast live on Fox Network.Supporters can vote by posting on the Miss Universe Twitter page using the #MissUniverse hashtag and the country of the contestant. Those who are not on Twitter can cast votes through vote.missuniverse.com.The candidates with the most votes will be in the top 12. South Africans have such a sense of pride that I believe that we can be in the top 12, Kunene said from Manila.KUTULLO MADISHA